• The University of Makati won 5 out of 7 prizes in the animation category at the 31st Gawad CCP para sa alternatibong pelikula at Vidyo or Gawad Alternatido
• Based on the FindUniversity.ph Weighted Board Exams Ranking University Of Makati is ranked 38/47 in all of Metro Manila, and ranked 177/273 out of all the school in the Philippines.
• Won 1 prize in the documentary category at the 31st Gawad CCP para sa alternatibong pelikula at Vidyo or Gawad Alternatido
• During the 2004 Athens Olympics Jasmin Figueroa an athlete of UMAK defeated the former World Champion Natalia Valeeva of Italy in archery. She also finished as a gold medalist at the South East Asian Games
• During 2002 Edwin Asoro led UMAK in the finals of NAASCU. Resulting in the drafting of Asoro by the Barako Bulls in the Philippine Basketball Association
• Rachelle Anne Cabral an archer of the University of Makati Achieved a Gold Medal in the South East Asian Games.
• Alyssa Dalida a squash athlete of the University of Makati represented the Philippines at the 16th Asian Games.
• Charlene Gillego was a draftee at Philippines Super Liga (PSL) and finished as the fourth pick.
- Performance in Licensure Board Examinations -
>> Consistently, UMak's percentage of passers in the Licensure Board Exams (CPA, Nursing, Teachers, Master Electrician, etc.) has been higher than the national passing rate.
>> College of Allied Health Studies produced numerous top-notchers in the nursing licensure examinations. Some of these students are Denise Claudia Mangiliman and Betty Chua Chung (College of Nursing batch 2007 graduates) placed fourth and fifth, respectively, in the December 2007 Nursing Board.
>> UMak 's Accountancy Program made history in October 2010 when 25 accounting students passed the CPA Licensure Exam: the most number of CPA passers in the history of UMak in one board exam taking. In the May 2011 CPA Board Exam, 10 UMak students passed for an outstanding 50% passing rate. 19 students passed the October 2011 CPA Board Examination. Kristofferson Isar Dela Cruz was ranked fifth out of 2,132 passers with a rating of 89.43%. UMak achieved a 56% passing rate (vs. 35.78% national passing rate) in the CPA Licensure Examination in 2015 in Manila, Baguio, Cagayan de Oro, Cebu, Davao, Iloilo and Legazpi.
